<section xml:id="prerequisites-for-test-execution" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                             xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                             xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Prerequisites for test execution</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="testExecViewContextId" xml:id="prerequisites-for-test-execution.testExecViewContextId">Test Suite Browser</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="runningAutsViewContextId" xml:id="prerequisites-for-test-execution.runningAutsViewContextId">Running AUTs View</anchor>
  <para>
    To be able to start a test you must:
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Create a Test Suite (<xref linkend="creating-a-test-suite"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Add Test Cases to be executed to the Test Suite
        (<xref linkend="adding-items-to-editors"/>)
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Define an AUT (<xref linkend="define-aut"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Configure an AUT (<xref linkend="configuringaut"/>) if you want to start
        the AUT from the ITE.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Choose an AUT for the Test Suite (<xref linkend="configuring-test-suites-in-the-properties-view"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Set the working language to the language you want to execute
        the test in.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Connect to the AUT Agent (<xref linkend="connect-aut-agent"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Start the AUT (<xref linkend="starting-the-aut"/>) (either from the ITE or using
        the <emphasis>autrun command</emphasis>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Complete object mapping (<xref linkend="object-mapping-1"/>).
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Make sure that your test data is complete in your Test
        Cases.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
  <para role="tip">
    It is a good idea to set your preferences for test
    results in the preferences dialog (<xref linkend="gdprefs"/>) before
    test execution.
  </para>
</section>